sfField.summary: User-defined unique identifier for this account, up to 30 characters in length. Must be unique within a given Financial Company.

Defines how this account may be used in AP. Options are

Accounts Payable
Accrued Accounts Payable
Cash
Credit Card Clearing
Foreign Exchange Variance
Freight
Tax
Defines how this account may be used in AR. See dropdown for options to select from.
This field is used to categorize GL Accounts within their specified Account Type
This field is used to further categorize GL Accounts within the their designated Category 1
This field is used to further categorize GL Accounts within the their designated Category 2
This field allows for each GL Account to be associated with one of the Cash Flow Report Sections. All accounts with the same Cash Flow Section value will be included in that section of the report.

sfPLE.n: Acquisition of subsidiaries, net of cash acquired
Depreciation of property, plant and equipment (excluding right-of-use assets)
Dividends paid to equity shareholders of the Parent
Effect of exchange rates on cash and cash equivalents
Loss on disposal of property, plant and equipment
Net cash flow from trade and other payables (including contract liabilities)
Net cash flow from trade and other receivables (including contract assets)
Proceeds from disposal of property, plant and equipment
Purchases of property, plant and equipment
Repayment of capital element of finance leases

sfField.summary: This field contains the Cash Flow Section value for this account in an index field
An optional, free-form field up to 30 characters in length whose only use is in user-created Salesforce reports.
The Financial Company for which this GL Account pertains

Defines type of control account this is. Once used in a transaction, value cannot be changed. Options are

Not a Control Account
Accounts Receivable Account
Accounts Payable Account
On-Hand Inventory
WIP Inventory
Combined On-Hand and WIP Inventory
Income Tax Account

User-defined description of this GL Account, up to 100 characters in length. Note that when GL Accounts are used, they typically display with the Account Number followed by the description in parenthesis. Example: 1001 (Cash - General)
When checked, when running GL Transaction Inquiry, additional columns will be added to the right of the standard columns, displaying AP-related transaction details.
When checked, when running GL Transaction Inquiry, additional columns will be added to the right of the standard columns, displaying AR-related transaction details.
When checked, when running GL Transaction Inquiry, additional columns will be added to the right of the standard columns, displaying Cost Transaction-related transaction details.
When checked, indicates this Account is associated with one or more Fixed Assets - and when used on certain transactions, the system will require an Asset ID be specified.
This picklist controls how the UFX process treats this account.

sfField.t: GL Txn Inquiry Detail Field Set

sfField.summary: When checked, indicates that this Account is no longer active & can't be selected for use. If the Account is already used on a control record, transactions using this account will still process. If not acceptable, change control records where used.
Identifies whether the normal balance carried for this Account is a Debit or a Credit balance

If checked, this Capital account represents prior-years’ retained earnings. This field should be accurate if the company participates in a multi-currency consolidation; otherwise, it doesn’t matter if it’s check or unchecked.

Defines the type of GL Account for this record, driving how this account is used in Financial reporting. Note that once used in a transaction, value cannot be changed. Options are

Asset
Liability
Capital
Revenue
Expense

For companies doing business in countries that collect Value Added Tax (VAT)

Options are
 
--None-- (appropriate for companies that will not create any VAT transactions)
Not a VAT Account
Incoming VAT
Outgoing VAT
Both Incoming and Outgoing
This field provides a reference to the associated GL Account in the Parent Company for Accounts in a Subsidiary Company.
sfField.t: Associated GL Account in Parent Company
